cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a new method for removing raindrops from single images using a neural network architecture. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of problem-specific knowledge and the simplification of the learning process, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves feature fusion and color space transformation, which could also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
